About this item

  • Hide lines and wrinkles: Coty Airspun face powder in translucent extra coverage is a loose face and setting powder that helps to minimize the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, acne, scars and other blemishes, giving your facial skin a smoother, softer look
  • Foundation or setting powder: Coty Airspun face powder can be used to help smooth and soften the appearance of your skin as a foundation coverage, or use the loose powder on top of your makeup as a setting powder so you can get that flawless, smooth look
  • Lightweight long lasting coverage: Airspun Loose Face Powder is long lasting and helps give full coverage that feels lightweight enough to wear all day. This face powder can be used as a foundation or setting powder and helps your face look smooth and flawless
  • Flawless finish: Get the flawless finish you want with the help of Airspun loose face powder. Use to set contouring and highlights, or to help conceal and reduce the look of rough skin, fine lines, wrinkles, skin blemishes and help correct uneven skin tones

From the manufacturer

Coty Airspun

Coty Airspun powder has been one of the best kept beauty secrets since 1935. Airspun is a loose face powder that's blended with air to create a lightweight, velvety finish. This finely milled powder hides lines, wrinkles and blemishes leaving a flawless finish. Airspun can be used for 'baking' highlight and contour, setting makeup or even applying as a foundation. This timeless powder is a must-have for any beauty lover.

How to Use Airspun to 'Bake' Concealer

Apply Concealer

Apply your favorite concealer, blending it under your eyes and along your t-zone. Let concealer dry.

Press & Sweep

Apply a layer of Coty Airspun and let it 'bake' or set for 5-10 minutes. Use a powder brush to sweep excess powder away.

Ready to Go

Enjoy your final look! Airspun is great to use for baking, contouring, and setting your makeup for all day or night wear.

Product Description

A Beauty Secret since 1935. The creation of a visionary Master Perfumer, Francois Coty, Airspun is a loose face powder blended with air, providing the ultimate in coverage with a lightweight feel. Today it is a must have for highlighting and contouring. Light as air and yet velvety soft, Airspun powder provides a truly flawless finish. Airspun is packaged in a unique round canister with a powder puff applicator. Featuring an exclusive microspun formula where loose powder particles are spun and swirled until they reach a cloud like softness. This ultra smooth powder hides tiny lines, winkles and blemishes and gives a new softness to your skin. Can be used to set makeup or as a foundation. Translucent loose face powder will hide tiny lines, wrinkles and blemishes. Regulates oil control and gives a magnifying look.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2023
Size: 2.3 Ounce (Pack of 1)Color: TranslucentVerified Purchase
I recently purchased the Coty Airspun Loose Face Powder in the Translucent shade and I am extremely impressed with its performance. This powder is a holy grail for setting makeup and achieving a flawless, airbrushed finish. The translucent shade is perfect for all skin tones as it blends seamlessly without altering the color of my foundation.

One of the standout features of this powder is its lightweight and finely milled texture. It feels incredibly soft on the skin and doesn't settle into fine lines or pores. It effortlessly mattifies the skin without leaving a heavy or cakey feeling. I also appreciate its long-lasting formula that keeps my makeup looking fresh and shine-free throughout the day.

The packaging of this loose powder is also noteworthy. The powder comes in a sturdy container with a classic puff applicator. The sifter dispenser ensures that I can easily control the amount of product I dispense without any mess. The powder itself has a light and pleasant scent that is not overpowering.

Overall, Coty Airspun Loose Face Powder in Translucent is a must-have in any makeup routine. Its ability to set makeup, control shine, and give a flawless finish is truly impressive. The affordable price and generous amount of product it offers make it a great value for the money. I highly recommend this powder to anyone looking for a reliable, high-performing loose face powder.

Sushi Girl
5.0 out of 5 stars Extra Coverage Translucent Powder on extremely oily skin
Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2018
Verified Purchase
Overall I'd say this extra coverage translucent powder is better than my Laura Mercier translucent powder. I've used this powder a dozen times since purchase so I have a pretty fair experience to review this now. For more details keep reading on.
Design: Upon arrival, I had no issues opening the plastic seal covering the sifter/holes containing the powder underneath. There was no leak, all product was contained. There's a big cotton puff, which I tossed because I'd never use it on the face knowing it can easily harbor bacteria and cause breakouts. I think it can simply serve as a mechanism to prevent spills or leaks, since the lid is not a screw top and a bit easy to come loose and the sifter has no other means of being sealed. Because of this, I'd never attempt to travel with this powder. The risk is far too high for what it's worth. I'd be mad if all my other toiletries were smeared with powder.
Effectiveness: color, coverage and duration of oil control are satisfactory for my extremely oily T zones, including forehead, nose, eyebrow areas, and cheek area surrounding the nose. I have sand colored complexion, and I prefer a matte and light toned skin. Highlighters look horrifying on my skin, that's how oily I am. This extra coverage powder has a pinkish tone when initially applied but I don't mind it. My skin looks matte right away. I do look a bit cakey if I examine my face closely, BUT same result using Laura Mercier translucent powder. With both powders, I usually use a damp beauty blender to apply a decent layer over my oily areas mentioned. After 6 hours, Airspun reveals some oil back to the face. See photos before and after 6 hrs. But again, Laura Mercier translucent powder revealed even more oil within the same timeframe. I find that Airspun does create more of a dust cloud though. Try not to breathe it in. Plus the scent is strong like baby powder. I don't mind it personally. I have not noticed additional breakouts caused by this powder on top of my usual breakouts.
Amount and price worth: huge amount of product, looks like it hasn't been touched after a dozen uses. I don't use a light hand either. I spent $10 on this, but I really don't mind because it's the extra coverage version and so much product, it will last me over a year for sure. And it's still 3x cheaper than Laura Mercier.
Overall, Laura Mercier doesn't compare in effectiveness and price, and the only reason I use it is for traveling, and to use it up before it expires. I'll only purchase Airspun from now on.
